   {:e #blake3 "4d7d6e94dc371910e11ee4b16a9ab280d6225cd4b6a04dfd0e54a6278e8dad24" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: End-to-end proof that C9 solves the original problem: an agent can synthesize accumulated observations without reading external documents. Must verify BOTH the proactive path (seed convergent findings) AND the reactive path (observe subcommands with steering-optimized output). UNIT TESTS FOR all_observations() (in concept.rs test section, 5 tests): (A) empty store returns empty vec. (B) store with 5 observations returns 5, sorted by timestamp descending. (C) fields correctly extracted: confidence, category, concept_name, agent_name, link_count. (D) observations with concept assignment show concept_name. (E) observations with :exploration/depends-on links have correct link_count. UNIT TESTS FOR observe subcommands (in observe.rs test section, 6 tests): (A) observe list groups by concept correctly. (B) observe search ranks by composite score (high-link, high-confidence observations first). (C) observe search with no matches returns empty. (D) observe show includes incoming and outgoing links. (E) observe recent respects limit. (F) observe TEXT creation still works (backward compat regression). UNIT TESTS FOR agent identity (in mod.rs test, 3 tests): (A) Default with no env var produces PID-based name. (B) BRAID_AGENT env overrides PID. (C) Explicit --agent overrides env. INTEGRATION TEST (tests/c9_second_order.rs, 2 scenarios): SCENARIO 1 (proactive path): Create store with 3 AgentIds each observing same finding. Verify find_agreement_clusters returns 3-agent cluster. Verify seed orientation contains Convergent findings. SCENARIO 2 (reactive path): Create store with 10 observations across 3 concepts with varying confidence and link counts. Verify observe list groups correctly. Verify observe search ranks by composite score. Verify observe show includes graph context. E2E SCRIPT (scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh, 12 checks with logging): (1) braid init in temp dir. (2) BRAID_AGENT=agent-1 braid observe 'F(S) stagnant at 0.62 for 13 sessions' -c 0.9. (3) BRAID_AGENT=agent-2 braid observe 'Fitness stuck at 0.62, verification sprint needed' -c 0.85. (4) BRAID_AGENT=agent-3 braid observe 'F(S) not moving, recommend verification work' -c 0.9. (5) braid observe 'Unrelated: C8 violation in schema.rs' -c 0.8. (6) braid observe list — ASSERT grouped output, F(S) cluster has 3+ members. (7) braid observe search 'stagnant' — ASSERT >= 2 results, highest-confidence first. (8) braid observe search 'unrelated' — ASSERT 1 result. (9) braid observe recent 2 — ASSERT exactly 2 shown with concept tags. (10) braid observe show <entity-from-step-2> — ASSERT full body + confidence + agent displayed. (11) braid seed --task 'synthesize' — ASSERT Convergent findings section with 3/3 agents. (12) ASSERT all exit codes 0. LOGGING: Each step logs: command, full stdout, full stderr, assertion pass/fail, elapsed time. On failure: dump store state (datom count, observation count by agent, concept inventory, agreement clusters). DEPENDS-ON: C9-P4 (t-266f06d5), C9-P5 (t-0217080c). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/tests/c9_second_order.rs, scripts/e2e_c9_complete.sh, inline tests in concept.rs and observe.rs. EFFORT: 5h." :op :assert}
